   =20
                  <h1 class=3D"title topictitle1" id=3D"ariaid-title1">User=
 Accounts for Devices</h1>
                  <section class=3D"body">
                     <p class=3D"p">Managed devices include a default <stro=
ng class=3D"ph b">admin</strong> account for CLI access. This chapter discu=
sses how
                        to create custom user accounts. See <a class=3D"xre=
f" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/conf=
iguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/logging_into_the_firepower_system.htm=
l#ID-2209-00000004">Logging into the Firepower System</a> for detailed info=
rmation about logging into the managed
                        device with a user account.
                     </p>
                  </section>
                  <!-- minitoc start -->
                  <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                     <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63482">About User Accounts f=
or Devices</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#Cisco_Reference.dita_9348b65b-4=
1fa-4fc8-9fd0-5d4381e66da6">Requirements and Prerequisites for User Account=
s for Devices</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#Cisco_Reference.dita_7224e5da-2=
dfd-45d8-87e5-74dbed79bebb">Guidelines and Limitations for User Accounts fo=
r Devices</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#task_r5y_zbr_qcb">Add an Intern=
al User at the CLI</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63531">Configure External Au=
thentication for the FTD</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#reference_lzr_kyq_qcb">Troubles=
hooting LDAP Authentication Connections</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc=
-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#reference_pzh_rsk_1gb">History =
for User Accounts for Devices</a></li>
                     </ul>
                  </nav>
                  <!-- minitoc end -->
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title2" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63482">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title2">A=
bout User Accounts for Devices</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">You can add custom user accounts on =
managed devices, either as internal users or, for the FTD, as
                           external users on a LDAP or RADIUS server. Each =
managed device maintains separate user
                           accounts. For example, when you add a user to th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, that user only h=
as access to the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>; y=
ou cannot then use that username to log directly into a managed device. You=
 must
                           separately add a user on the managed device.
                        </p>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                        <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63533">Internal and Exter=
nal Users</a></li>
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63534">CLI Access</a></li=
>
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63962">CLI User Roles</a>=
</li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title3" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63533">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
">Internal and External Users</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">Managed devices support two types=
 of users:</p>
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Internal user=E2=80=94The d=
evice checks a local database for user authentication. For
                                    more information about internal users, =
see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/securit=
y/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_devi=
ce.html#task_r5y_zbr_qcb">Add an Internal User at the CLI</a>. The FTD, NGI=
PSv, and ASA FirePOWER support internal
                                    users.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">External user (FTD only)=E2=
=80=94If the user is not present in the local database, the
                                    system queries an external LDAP or RADI=
US authentication server. For more
                                    information about external users, see <=
a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/fir=
epower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.ht=
ml#id_63531">Configure External Authentication for the FTD</a>. Only the FT=
D supports external users.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title4" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63534">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title4=
">CLI Access</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">Firepower devices include a Firep=
ower CLI that runs on top of Linux. You can create internal
                              users on devices using the CLI. You can estab=
lish external users
                              on FTD devices using the FMC. For detailed in=
formation about the
                              management UIs, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D=
"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/=
guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/logging_into_the_firepower_system.html#id_42565=
">Firepower System User Interfaces</a>.
                           </p>
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/caut.gif"><br><p><b>Caution</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Users with CLI Config=
 level access can access the Linux shell
                                          using the <span><span class=3D"ke=
yword kwd">expert</span> </span> command,
                                          and obtain <code class=3D"ph code=
ph">sudoers</code> privileges in
                                          the Linux shell, which can presen=
t a security risk.
                                          For system security reasons, we s=
trongly
                                          recommend:
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Only use the Li=
nux shell under TAC supervision
                                                or when explicitly instruct=
ed by Firepower user
                                                documentation.=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Make sure that =
you restrict the list
                                                of users with CLI access ap=
propriately.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">When granting C=
LI access privileges, restrict the list of users with Config level access.<=
/p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Do not add user=
s directly in the Linux shell; only use the procedures in this chapter.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Do not access F=
irepower devices using
                                                CLI expert mode unless dire=
cted by Cisco TAC or by
                                                explicit instructions in th=
e Firepower user
                                                documentation.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title5" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63962">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title5=
">CLI User Roles</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63962__ID-2263-0000150e"=
>On managed devices, user access to commands in the CLI depends on the role=
 you assign.</p>
                           <dl class=3D"dl">
                              <dt class=3D"dt dlterm"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol" id=3D"id_63962__ID-2263-00001512">None</span>
                                =20
                              </dt>
                              <dd class=3D"dd">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The user cannot log into th=
e device on the command line.</p>
                                =20
                              </dd>
                              <dt class=3D"dt dlterm"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol" id=3D"id_63962__ID-2263-00001517">Config</span>
                                =20
                              </dt>
                              <dd class=3D"dd">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The user can access all com=
mands, including configuration commands. Exercise caution in assigning this=
 level of access to
                                    users.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </dd>
                              <dt class=3D"dt dlterm"><span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol" id=3D"id_63962__ID-2263-0000151e">Basic</span>
                                =20
                              </dt>
                              <dd class=3D"dd">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The user can access non-con=
figuration commands only. Only internal users and
                                    <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Threat Defense</span></span> external RADIUS users support the Bas=
ic role.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </dd>
                           </dl>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title6" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.dita_9348b65b-41fa=
-4fc8-9fd0-5d4381e66da6">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title6">R=
equirements and Prerequisites for User Accounts for Devices</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_9348b65b-41fa-4fc8-9fd0-5d4381e66da6__d480875e330">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=3D"=
ph">Model Support</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span cl=
ass=3D"ph">FTD</span></span>=E2=80=94Internal and external users
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">ASA Fire=
POWER</span>=E2=80=94Internal users
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">NGIPSv</=
span>=E2=80=94Internal users
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_9348b65b-41fa-4fc8-9fd0-5d4381e66da6__d480875e365">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=3D"=
ph">Supported Domains</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">Any</span></p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_9348b65b-41fa-4fc8-9fd0-5d4381e66da6__d480875e376">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=3D"=
ph">User Roles</span></h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Configure external users=E2=80=94=
<span class=3D"ph">Admin</span> FMC user
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Configure internal users=E2=80=94=
Config CLI user</p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title7" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.dita_7224e5da-2dfd=
-45d8-87e5-74dbed79bebb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title7">G=
uidelines and Limitations for User Accounts for Devices</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"Cisco_Reference.di=
ta_7224e5da-2dfd-45d8-87e5-74dbed79bebb__d480875e420">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Defaults</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">All devices include an <strong cl=
ass=3D"ph b">admin</strong> user as a local user account; you cannot delete
                              the <strong class=3D"ph b">admin</strong> use=
r. The default initial password is <strong class=3D"ph b">Admin123</strong>=
; the system
                              forces you to change this during the initiali=
zation process. See the getting started
                              guide for your model for more information abo=
ut system initialization.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title8" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title8">A=
dd an Internal User at the CLI</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__context_DAE3B200C2DC4016BB2D7C5817AB590A">
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">Use the CLI to create internal us=
ers on the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</=
span></span>, <span class=3D"ph">ASA FirePOWER</span>, and <span class=3D"p=
h">NGIPSv</span> devices.
                           </p>
                           	=09
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">
                           <tbody>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb_=
_step_2D9EDBF101EE4FDAB7ADBBCB683EF720">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Log into the device=
 CLI using an account with Config privileges.</p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">The <strong class=3D"=
ph b">admin</strong> user account has the required privileges, but any acco=
unt with Config privileges will work. You can use an SSH session or
                                          the Console port.
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">For certain the <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> mod=
els, the Console port puts you into the FXOS CLI. Use the <span><span class=
=3D"keyword kwd">connect ftd</span> </span> command to get to the <span cla=
ss=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> CLI.=20
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb_=
_step_ABFEF1EF873C486ABDD5D52F0E78F8E0">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Create the user acc=
ount.</p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span><span class=3D"=
keyword kwd">configure user add</span>
                                             							<var>username</var> {<s=
pan class=3D"keyword kwd">basic</span> | <span class=3D"keyword kwd">config=
</span>} </span>
                                          				=09
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><var>user=
name</var> </span>=E2=80=94Sets the username. The username must be Linux-va=
lid:
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                   								=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Maximum 3=
2 alphanumeric characters, plus hyphen (-) and underscore (_)</p>
                                                   							=09
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                   								=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p">All lower=
case</p>
                                                   							=09
                                                </li>
                                                <li class=3D"li">
                                                   								=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Cannot st=
art with hyphen (-); cannot be all numbers; cannot include a period(.), at =
sign (@), or slash (/)</p>
                                                   							=09
                                                </li>
                                             </ul>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_1C2DC48568414D9EAC69FC7FB1F4E8C4">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">basic</span> </span>=E2=80=94Gives the user basic access=
. This role does not allow the user to enter configuration commands.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_E23E67E8FB3F40B3BEBE1DE48926E224">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">config</span> </span>=E2=80=94Gives the user configurati=
on access. This role gives the user full administrator rights to all comman=
ds.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp">
                                       <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                          <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h3>
                                       </section>
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qc=
b__ID-3858-00000d2d">The following example adds a user account named johncr=
ichton with Config access rights. The password is not shown as you type
                                          it.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					<pre class=3D"pre codeblock" id=
=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb__ID-3858-00000d2e"><code>
&gt; <kbd class=3D"userinput"><b class=3D"ph userinput">configure user add =
johncrichton config</b></kbd>
Enter new password for user johncrichton: <kbd class=3D"userinput"><b class=
=3D"ph userinput">newpassword</b></kbd>
Confirm new password for user johncrichton: <kbd class=3D"userinput"><b cla=
ss=3D"ph userinput">newpassword</b></kbd>
&gt; <kbd class=3D"userinput"><b class=3D"ph userinput">show user</b></kbd>
Login              UID   Auth Access  Enabled Reset    Exp Warn  Str Lock M=
ax
admin             1000  Local Config  Enabled    No  Never  N/A  Dis   No N=
/A
johncrichton      1001  Local Config  Enabled    No  Never  N/A  Dis   No  =
 5

</code></pre>
                                       					<div class=3D"tableContainer"><=
table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                          <tbody><tr>
                                             <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"td_f=
aq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                             </td>
                                             <td border=3D"0" class=3D"td_f=
aq">
                                                <section class=3D"note__con=
tent">
                                                   					=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Tell user=
s they can change their own passwords using the <span><span class=3D"keywor=
d kwd">configure password</span> </span> command.=20
                                                   </p>
                                                   				=09
                                                </section>
                                             </td>
                                          </tr>
                                       </tbody></table></div>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb_=
_step_C5C4890F4F9C4C1E984938EBC11AE5A8">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional) Adjust t=
he characteristics of the account to meet your security requirements. </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can use the follo=
wing commands to change the default account behavior. </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_29CCFA05A5C340B78243C0A98A1207FA">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user aging</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kbd>=
<var>username max_days warn_days</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Sets an expirat=
ion date for the user's password. Specify the maximum number of days for th=
e password to be valid followed
                                                by the number of days befor=
e expiration the user will be warned about the upcoming expiration. Both va=
lues are 1 to 9999,
                                                but the warning days must b=
e less than the maximum days. When you create the account, there is no expi=
ration date for the
                                                password.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_5A7C35C067714B4C982E232A0F37DC86">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user forcereset</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> <=
/kbd><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Forces the user=
 to change the password on the next login. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_E69E08333710415C8E89D02CCFEBCA8D">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user maxfailedlogins</span><kbd class=3D"ph se=
p"> </kbd><var>username number</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Sets the maximu=
m number of consecutive failed logins you will allow before locking the acc=
ount, from 1 to 9999. Use the <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configure u=
ser unlock</span> </span> command to unlock accounts. The default for new a=
ccounts is 5 consecutive failed logins.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_07A8D8D45AF04884AED1A36CFF2086CF">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user minpasswdlen</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep">=
 </kbd><var>username number</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Sets a minimum =
password length, which can be from 1 to 127. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_1E7CAC42102E40A6A1E52280EB2B9DC9">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user strengthcheck</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"=
> </kbd><var>username</var><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> { </kbd><span class=3D"ke=
yword kwd">enable</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> |  </kbd><span class=3D"keyw=
ord kwd">disable</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep">} </kbd> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Enables or disa=
bles password strength checking, which requires a user to meet specific pas=
sword criteria when changing their
                                                password. When a user=E2=80=
=99s password expires or if the <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configure=
 user forcereset</span> </span> command is used, this requirement is automa=
tically enabled the next time the user logs in.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_r5y_zbr_qcb_=
_step_6BA69CC1B90F4E57A2ABE942C61A7D8C">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Manage user account=
s as necessary. </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">Users can get locked =
out of their accounts, or you might need to remove accounts or fix other is=
sues. Use the following commands
                                          to manage the user accounts on th=
e system.=20
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_F05D3E4ACDDC49CB9A7F221CCEEE0A56">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user access</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kbd=
><var> username</var><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> { </kbd><span class=3D"keyword =
kwd">basic</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> |  </kbd><span class=3D"keyword kwd=
">config</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep">} </kbd> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Changes the pri=
vileges for a user account. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_114A1FBF997C4F86925634FB26F90B0C">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user delete</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kbd=
><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Deletes the spe=
cified account. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_944BDC0C4F904F8A94999E85721BBA95">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user disable</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kb=
d><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Disables the sp=
ecified account without deleting it. The user cannot log in until you enabl=
e the account. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_6EDD80A0F7AA440698EBB144F4845A4A">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user enable</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kbd=
><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Enables the spe=
cified account. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_40C1EFB522804625B356E624BA0D533D">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user password</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </k=
bd><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Changes the pas=
sword for the specified user. Users should normally change their own passwo=
rd using the <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configure password</span> </=
span> command.=20
                                             </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li" id=3D"task_r5y_z=
br_qcb__li_5E49456C361D420BB433B254B65537FE">
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span><span cla=
ss=3D"keyword kwd">configure user unlock</span><kbd class=3D"ph sep"> </kbd=
><var>username</var> </span>
                                                						=09
                                             </p>
                                             						=09
                                             <p class=3D"p">Unlocks a user =
account that was locked due to exceeding the maximum number of consecutive =
failed login attempts. </p>
                                             					=09
                                          </li>
                                       </ul>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody>
                        </table></div>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title9" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63531">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title9">C=
onfigure External Authentication for the FTD</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">To enable external authentication fo=
r FTD devices, you need to add one or more external
                           authentication objects.
                        </p>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                        <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63601">About External Aut=
hentication for the FTD</a></li>
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63679">Add an LDAP Extern=
al Authentication Object for FTD</a></li>
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63677">Add a RADIUS Exter=
nal Authentication Object for FTD</a></li>
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63679">Enable External Au=
thentication for Users on FTD Devices</a></li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title10" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63601">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
0">About External Authentication for the FTD</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63601__ID-2258-000001d2"=
>When you enable external authentication for FTD users, the FTD
                              verifies the user credentials with an LDAP or=
 RADIUS server as specified in an
                              <em class=3D"ph i">external authentication ob=
ject</em>.=20
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">External authentication objects c=
an be used by the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> a=
nd <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></s=
pan> devices. You can share the same object between the different
                              appliance/device types, or create separate ob=
jects. For the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defen=
se</span></span>, you can only activate one external authentication object =
in
                              the platform settings that you deploy to the =
devices.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">The timeout range is =
different for the FTD and the FMC, so if you share an object, be
                                          sure not to exceed the FTD's smal=
ler timeout range (1-30 seconds for LDAP, and 1-300
                                          seconds for RADIUS). If you set t=
he timeout to a higher value, the FTD external
                                          authentication configuration will=
 not work.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">External authenticati=
on is not supported on <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Thre=
at Defense</span></span> virtual devices.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Only a subset of fields in the ex=
ternal authentication object are used for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> SSH access. If you fill in addi=
tional fields, they are ignored.
                              If you also use this object for other device =
types, those fields will be used.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">LDAP users always have Config pri=
vileges. RADIUS users can be defined as either Config or
                              Basic users.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You can either define users on th=
e RADIUS server (with the Service-Type attribute), or
                              you can pre-define the user list in the exter=
nal authentication object. For LDAP, you
                              can specify a filter to match CLI users on th=
e LDAP server.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>Users with CLI access can gain L=
inux shell access with the <span class=3D"keyword cmdname">expert</span>
                                       command. Linux shell users can obtai=
n root privileges, which can present a security
                                       risk. Make sure that you:
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Restrict the li=
st of users with Linux shell access.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Do not create L=
inux shell users.</p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>

e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63721">About LDAP</a><=
/li>
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63722">About RADIUS</a=
></li>

                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title11" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63721">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le11">About LDAP</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63721__d752e12">The L=
ightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) allows you
                                 to set up a directory on your network that=
 organizes objects, such as user
                                 credentials, in a centralized location. Mu=
ltiple applications can then
                                 access those credentials and the informati=
on used to describe them. If you
                                 ever need to change a user's credentials, =
you can change them in one
                                 place.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"> Microsoft has announced that =
Active
                                 Directory servers will start enforcing LDA=
P binding and LDAP signing
                                 in 2020. Microsoft is making these a requi=
rement because when using
                                 default settings, an elevation of privileg=
e vulnerability exists in
                                 Microsoft Windows that could allow a man-i=
n-the-middle attacker to
                                 successfully forward an authentication req=
uest to a Windows LDAP
                                 server. For more information, see <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4520412/2020-lda=
p-channel-binding-and-ldap-signing-requirement-for-windows" target=3D"_blan=
k">2020 LDAP channel binding and
                                    LDAP signing requirement for Windows</a=
> on the Microsoft
                                 support site.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you have not done so alread=
y, we recommend you start using TLS/SSL encryption to authenticate with an
                                 Active Directory server.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title12" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63722">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le12">About RADIUS</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63722__d188e12">Remot=
e Authentication Dial In User Service (RADIUS) is an
                                 authentication protocol used to authentica=
te, authorize, and account for user access to
                                 network resources. You can create an authe=
ntication object for any RADIUS server that
                                 conforms to <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http=
s://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2865" target=3D"_blank">RFC 2865</a>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63722__d188e18">Firep=
ower devices support the use of SecurID tokens. When you
                                 configure authentication by a server using=
 SecurID, users authenticated against that
                                 server append the SecurID token to the end=
 of their SecurID PIN and use that as their
                                 password when they log in. You do not need=
 to configure anything extra on the Firepower
                                 device to support SecurID.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title13" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63679">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
3">Add an LDAP External Authentication Object for FTD</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_6367=
9__context_B1E773CCA8184882B8ECFDC990574DB1">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Add an LDAP server to support =
external users for FTD management.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">In a multid=
omain deployment, external authentication objects are only available in the=
 domain in which they are created.</span>
                                =20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Sharing=
 External Authentication Objects</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">External LDAP objects can be u=
sed by the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> and <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> de=
vices. You can share the same object between the <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> and devices, or create separate objects.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">For LDAP, the time=
out range is different for the FTD and the FMC, so if you share
                                             an object, be sure not to exce=
ed the FTD's smaller timeout range (1-30 seconds).
                                             If you set the timeout to a hi=
gher value, the deployment to the FTD will
                                             fail.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b"><span c=
lass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> Suppo=
rted Fields</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Only a subset of fields in the=
 LDAP object are used for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower T=
hreat Defense</span></span> SSH access. If you fill in additional fields, t=
hey are
                                 ignored. If you also use this object for t=
he FMC, those fields will be used. This
                                 procedure only covers the supported fields=
 for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</sp=
an></span>. For other fields, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-confi=
g-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63679">Add an LDAP External Authen=
tication Object for FMC</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Usernam=
es</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Usernames must be Linux-valid =
usernames and be lower-case only, using alphanumeric
                                 characters plus period (.) or hyphen (-). =
Other special characters such as at sign
                                 (@) and slash (/) are not supported. You c=
annot add the <strong class=3D"ph b">admin</strong> user for
                                 external authentication. You can only add =
external users (as part of the External
                                 Authentication object) in the <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>; you cannot add them at the CL=
I. Note that internal users can only be added at
                                 the CLI, not in the <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you previously configured t=
he same username for an internal user using the
                                 <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configur=
e user add</span> </span> command, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> first checks the password against =
the internal user, and if that fails, it checks
                                 the LDAP server. Note that you cannot late=
r add an internal user with the same name
                                 as an external user; only pre-existing int=
ernal users are supported.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Privile=
ge Level</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">LDAP users always have Config =
privileges.</p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"id_636=
79__d480875e1114">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You must specify DNS server(s)=
 for domain name lookup on your device. Even if you
                                 specify an IP address and not a hostname f=
or the LDAP server on this procedure, the
                                 LDAP server may return a URI for authentic=
ation that can include a hostname. A DNS
                                 lookup is required to resolve the hostname=
. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secur=
ity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_managemen=
t_basics.html#id_46848">Modify Device Management Interfaces at the CLI</a> =
to add DNS servers.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_91EF10ECE6554C49B66A3EAC724E64E8">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63679__=
ID-2263-000002a4">Choose <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade">=
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol=
"> Users</span></span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>

_DE9E817D2129423B92BFCC910AC85E33">

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63679__=
ID-2263-000002a7">Click the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID=
-2263-000002a9">External Authentication</span> tab.=20

_BCCA4F1939B2432E889E4183817B1598">

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
