r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63679__=
ID-2263-000002aa">Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-226=
3-000002ac">Add External Authentication Object</span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_BDFF4390139C4A10BAA0BFDFC71AF560">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Set the <span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol">Authentication Method</span> to <span class=3D"ph uico=
ntrol">LDAP</span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_907E5DAD056B4D92BC2CB0DD575448C9">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter a <span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002b9">Name</span> and opti=
onal <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002ba">Descrip=
tion</span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Choose a <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002bd">Server Type</span> =
from the drop-down list.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_85F8C68041CC416DA6976089F9485360">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;7</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">For the <span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol">Primary Server</span>, enter a <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002c2">Host Name/IP Address</span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID=
-2263-000002c3">If you are using a certificate to connect via TLS or SSL, t=
he host name in the certificate must match the host name used in
                                             this field. In addition, IPv6 =
addresses are not supported for encrypted connections.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_A9E51474DA5744AF8E1E1F7CE6C12368">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional) Chang=
e the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002c7">Port</=
span> from the default.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_A897C2D99BA1436583F85BCB17C93F9B">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;9</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional) Enter=
 the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Backup Server</span> parameters.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_36ED2C64FBC7417F87C73C5DDCCC1E0A">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;10</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">LDAP-Specific Parameters</span>.
                                       </p>
                                       <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol substeps"=
>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter the =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Base DN</span> for the LDAP directory you want=
 to access. For example, to authenticate names in the Security organization=
 at the Example
                                                company, enter <code class=
=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000384">ou=3Dsecurity,dc=3Dexample=
,dc=3Dcom</code>. Alternatively click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id=
_63679__ID-2263-00000380">Fetch DNs</span>, and choose the appropriate base=
 distinguished name from the drop-down list.=20
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional)=
 Enter the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000387">B=
ase Filter</span>. For example, if the user objects in a directory tree hav=
e a <code class=3D"ph codeph">physicalDeliveryOfficeName</code> attribute a=
nd users in the New York office have an attribute value of <code class=3D"p=
h codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000388">NewYork</code> for that attribu=
te, to retrieve only users in the New York office, enter <code class=3D"ph =
codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000389">(physicalDeliveryOfficeName=3DNew=
York)</code>.=20
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter a <s=
pan class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000038c">User Name</spa=
n> for a user who has sufficient credentials to browse the LDAP server. For=
 example, if you are connecting to an OpenLDAP server
                                                where user objects have a <=
code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000038e">uid</code> attri=
bute, and the object for the administrator in the Security division at your=
 example company has a <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00=
00038f">uid</code> value of <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-22=
63-00000390">NetworkAdmin</code>, you might enter <code class=3D"ph codeph"=
 id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000391">uid=3DNetworkAdmin,ou=3Dsecurity,dc=3Dex=
ample,dc=3Dcom.</code>
                                               =20
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter the =
user password in the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0=
000038d">Password</span> and the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Confirm Passw=
ord</span> fields.
                                             </p>
                                          </li>
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional)=
 Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000039c">Show =
Advanced Options</span> to configure the following advanced options.
                                             </p>
                                             <section class=3D"itemgroup in=
fo">
                                               =20
                                                <ul class=3D"ul">
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p"><span =
class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000003a5">Encryption</span>=
=E2=80=94Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">None</span>, <span class=3D"ph =
uicontrol">TLS</span>, or <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">SSL</span>.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p" id=3D"=
id_63679__ID-2263-000003a6">If you change the encryption method after speci=
fying a port, you reset the port to the default value for that method. For
                                                         <span class=3D"ph =
uicontrol">None</span> or <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">TLS</span>, the port=
 resets to the default value of 389. If you choose SSL encryption, the port=
 resets to 636.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p"><span =
class=3D"ph uicontrol">SSL Certificate Upload Path</span>=E2=80=94For SSL o=
r TLS encryption, you must choose a certificate by clicking <span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol">Choose File</span>.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p" id=3D"=
id_63679__ID-2263-000003ab">If you previously uploaded a certificate and wa=
nt to replace it, upload the new certificate and redeploy the configuration
                                                         to your devices to=
 copy over the new certificate.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                      <table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                                         <tbody><tr>
                                                            <td width=3D"1%=
" class=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                               <p><b>Note</=
b></p>&nbsp;
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td border=3D"0=
" class=3D"td_faq">
                                                               <section cla=
ss=3D"note__content">
                                                                 =20
                                                                  <p class=
=3D"p">TLS encryption requires a certificate on all platforms. For SSL, the=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></spa=
n> also requires a certificate. For other platforms, SSL does not require a=
 certificate. However, we recommend that you <em class=3D"ph i">always</em>=
 upload a certificate for SSL to prevent man-in-the-middle attacks.
                                                                  </p>
                                                                 =20
                                                               </section>
                                                            </td>
                                                         </tr>
                                                      </tbody></table>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                  =20
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">(Not U=
sed) <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000003af">User Na=
me
                                                            Template</span>=
=E2=80=94Not used by the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Th=
reat Defense</span></span>.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                   <li class=3D"li">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p"><span =
class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000003bb">Timeout</span>=E2=
=80=94Enter
                                                         the number of seco=
nds before rolling over to the backup
                                                         connection, betwee=
n 1 and 30. The default is 30.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                      <table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                                         <tbody><tr>
                                                            <td width=3D"1%=
" class=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                               <p><b>Note</=
b></p>&nbsp;
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td border=3D"0=
" class=3D"td_faq">
                                                               <section cla=
ss=3D"note__content">
                                                                 =20
                                                                  <p class=
=3D"p">The timeout range is different for the FTD and the FMC,
                                                                     so if =
you share an object, be sure not to exceed the
                                                                     FTD's =
smaller timeout range (1-30 seconds). If you set
                                                                     the ti=
meout to a higher value, the FTD LDAP
                                                                     config=
uration will not work.
                                                                  </p>
                                                                 =20
                                                               </section>
                                                            </td>
                                                         </tr>
                                                      </tbody></table>
                                                     =20
                                                   </li>
                                                </ul>
                                               =20
                                             </section>
                                          </li>
                                       </ol>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;11</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">(Optional) Set t=
he <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000494">CLI Acces=
s
                                             Attribute</span> if you
                                          want to use a <span class=3D"ph">=
CLI </span>access attribute other than the user
                                          distinguished type. For example, =
on a Microsoft Active Directory Server, use the
                                          <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"i=
d_63679__ID-2263-0000048d">sAMAccountName</code>
                                         =20
                                          <span class=3D"ph">CLI</span> acc=
ess attribute to retrieve=20
                                          <span class=3D"ph">CLI</span> acc=
ess users by typing <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000=
48e">sAMAccountName</code> in the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_636=
79__ID-2263-00000494_d1707e362a1310">CLI Access
                                             Attribute</span>
                                          field.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">Users =
with CLI access can gain Linux shell access with the
                                                         <span class=3D"key=
word cmdname">expert</span> command. Linux shell users can obtain root
                                                         privileges, which =
can present a security risk. Make sure that you
                                                         restrict the list =
of users with CLI or Linux shell access.
                                                        =20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63679__step=
_C2A7691BF4CC4528B5D08894DECEDAB1">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;12</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63679__=
ID-2263-00000490">Set the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2=
263-00000494_d1707e382a1310">CLI Access Filter</span>.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Choose one of the =
following methods:</p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">To use the s=
ame filter you specified when configuring authentication
                                                   settings, choose <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000049a">Same as Base
                                                      Filter</span>.=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">To retrieve =
administrative user entries based on attribute value,
                                                   enter the attribute name=
, a comparison operator, and the attribute
                                                   value you want to use as=
 a filter, enclosed in parentheses. For
                                                   example, if all network =
administrators have a <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000=
00495">manager</code> attribute which has an
                                                   attribute value of <code=
 class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000496">shell</code>, you
                                                   can set a base filter of=
 <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000497">(manager=3Dshe=
ll)</code>.=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">The usernames must=
 be Linux-valid:</p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Maximum 32 a=
lphanumeric characters, plus hyphen (-) and underscore
                                                   (_)
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">All lowercas=
e</p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Cannot start=
 with hyphen (-); cannot be all numbers; cannot include a
                                                   period (.), at sign (@),=
 or slash (/)
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">If you=
 previously configured the same username for an internal user, the
                                                         <span class=3D"ph"=
><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> first checks the=
 password against the internal user, and if that
                                                         fails, it checks t=
he LDAP server. Note that you cannot later add an
                                                         internal user with=
 the same name as an external user; only pre-existing
                                                         internal users are=
 supported.=20
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;13</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Save</span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;14</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enable use of th=
is server. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/d=
ocs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/platfor=
m_settings_for_firepower_threat_defense.html#task_hx5_5hy_1cb">Configure Ex=
ternal Authentication for SSH</a>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;15</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">If you later add=
 or delete users on the LDAP server, you must refresh the user
                                          list and redeploy the Platform Se=
ttings on managed devices.
                                       </p>
                                       <ol type=3D"a" class=3D"ol substeps"=
>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click the =
<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Refresh</span> (<a href=3D"=
https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/440001-450000/447001-4=
48000/447857.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"refresh icon"><img cl=
ass=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/4=
40001-450000/447001-448000/447857.jpg" alt=3D"refresh icon"></a>)</span> ne=
xt to each LDAP server.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <section class=3D"itemgroup in=
fo">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">If the user =
list changed, you will see a message advising you to
                                                   deploy configuration cha=
nges for your device.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </section>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li substep substepex=
pand">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd"><span clas=
s=3D"ph" id=3D"id_63679__ph_deploy_config_changes">Deploy configuration cha=
nges; see
                                                   <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/policy_management.html#task_75E181687ECF4EFC=
8EB6AF4509C20C0B">Deploy Configuration Changes</a>.</span></p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ol>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"example" id=3D"id_63679__examp=
le_D04F006377924EF08519F6807937FD7A">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Examples</h4=
>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Basic E=
xample</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001=
c1">The following figures illustrate a basic configuration of an LDAP login=
 authentication object for a Microsoft Active Directory
                                 Server. The LDAP server in this example ha=
s an IP address of 10.11.3.4. The connection uses port 389 for access.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456108.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456108.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001=
c6">This example shows a connection using a base distinguished name of <cod=
e class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001c7">OU=3Dsecurity,DC=3D=
it,DC=3Dexample,DC=3Dcom</code> for the security organization in the inform=
ation technology domain of the Example company.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456109.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456109.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001=
d7">A <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">CLI Access
                                    Attribute</span> of <code class=3D"ph c=
odeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001d8">sAMAccountName</code>
                                 causes each <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=
=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001d9">sAMAccountName</code> attribute to be
                                 checked for all objects in the directory f=
or matches when a user logs into the FTD.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000001=
da">Note that because no base filter is applied to this server, the
                                 FTD checks attributes for all objects in t=
he directory indicated by the base
                                 distinguished name. Connections to the ser=
ver time out after the default time period
                                 (or the timeout period set on the LDAP ser=
ver).=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Advance=
d Example</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
26">This example illustrates an advanced configuration of an LDAP login aut=
hentication object for a Microsoft Active Directory
                                 Server. The LDAP server in this example ha=
s an IP address of 10.11.3.4. The connection uses port 636 for access.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456110.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456110.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
2b">This example shows a connection using a base distinguished name of <cod=
e class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000022c">OU=3Dsecurity,DC=3D=
it,DC=3Dexample,DC=3Dcom</code> for the security organization in the inform=
ation technology domain of the Example company. However, note that this ser=
ver
                                 has a base filter of <code class=3D"ph cod=
eph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000230">(cn=3D*smith)</code>. The filter res=
tricts the users retrieved from the server to those with a common name endi=
ng in <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000231">smith</co=
de>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456111.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456111.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
36">The connection to the server is encrypted using SSL and a certificate n=
amed <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000237">certificat=
e.pem</code> is used for the connection. In addition, connections to the se=
rver time out after 60 seconds because of the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" =
id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000238">Timeout</span> setting.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
39">Because this server is a Microsoft Active Directory server, it
                                 uses the <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"i=
d_63679__ID-2263-0000023a">sAMAccountName</code> attribute to store
                                 user names rather than the <code class=3D"=
ph codeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-0000023b">uid</code> attribute.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
40">The <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">CLI Access
                                    Atrribute</span> of <code class=3D"ph c=
odeph" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000241">sAMAccountName</code>
                                 causes each <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=
=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-00000242">sAMAccountName</code> attribute to be
                                 checked for all objects in the directory f=
or matches when a user logs into the FTD.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63679__ID-2263-000002=
4d">In the following example, the <span class=3D"ph">CLI</span> access filt=
er is set to be the same as the base filter.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456113.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456113.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>

nav>

                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title14" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63677">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
4">Add a RADIUS External Authentication Object for FTD</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_6367=
7__d480875e1753">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Add a RADIUS server to support=
 external users for the FTD.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">In a multid=
omain deployment, external authentication objects are only available in the=
 domain in which they are created.</span>
                                =20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Sharing=
 External Authentication Objects</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You can share the same object =
between the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> and dev=
ices, or create separate objects. Note that the <span class=3D"ph"><span cl=
ass=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> supports defining users o=
n the RADIUS server, while the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</s=
pan></span> requires you to predefine the user list in the external authent=
ication object.
                                 You can choose to use the predefined list =
method for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defen=
se</span></span>, but if you want to define users on the RADIUS server, you
                                 must create separate objects for the <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> and=
 the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">The timeout range =
is different for the FTD and the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC<=
/span></span>, so if you share an object, be sure not to exceed the FTD's s=
maller timeout
                                             range (1-300 seconds). If you =
set the timeout to a higher value, the FTD RADIUS
                                             configuration will not work.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b"><span c=
lass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> Suppo=
rted Fields</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Only a subset of fields in the=
 RADIUS object are used for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower=
 Threat Defense</span></span> SSH access. If you fill in additional fields,=
 they are
                                 ignored. If you also use this object for t=
he FMC, those fields will be used. This
                                 procedure only covers the supported fields=
 for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</sp=
an></span>. For other fields, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cis=
co.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-confi=
g-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63677">Add a RADIUS External Authe=
ntication Object for FMC</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Usernam=
es</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You cannot add the <strong cla=
ss=3D"ph b">admin</strong> user for external authentication. You can only a=
dd
                                 external users (as part of the External Au=
thentication object) in the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span=
></span>; you cannot add them at the CLI. Note that internal users can only=
 be added at
                                 the CLI, not in the <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you previously configured t=
he same username for an internal user using the
                                 <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configur=
e user add</span> </span> command, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> first checks the password against =
the internal user, and if that fails, it checks
                                 the RADIUS server. Note that you cannot la=
ter add an internal user with the same
                                 name as an external user; only pre-existin=
g internal users are supported. For users
                                 defined on the RADIUS server, be sure to s=
et the privilege level to be the same as
                                 any internal users; otherwise you cannot l=
og in using the external user
                                 password.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_63677__step=
_define_users">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Define users on =
the RADIUS server using the Service-Type attribute.</p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">The following are =
supported values for the Service-Type attribute:</p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Administrato=
r (6)=E2=80=94Provides Config access authorization to the CLI.
                                                   These users can use all =
commands in the CLI.=20
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">NAS Prompt (=
7) or any level other than 6=E2=80=94Provides Basic access
                                                   authorization to the CLI=
. These users can use read-only commands,
                                                   such as <span class=3D"p=
h uicontrol">show</span> commands, for monitoring and
                                                   troubleshooting purposes=
.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">The names must be =
Linux-valid usernames:</p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Maximum 32 a=
lphanumeric characters, plus hyphen (-) and underscore
                                                   (_)
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">All lowercas=
e</p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Cannot start=
 with hyphen (-); cannot be all numbers; cannot include=20
                                                   <span class=3D"ph">at si=
gn (@) or slash (/)</span></p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Alternatively, you=
 can predefine users in the external authentication object
                                             (see Step <a class=3D"xref" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configura=
tion/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device.html#id_63677__step_s=
hell_access_filter">Step&nbsp;12</a>). To use the same RADIUS server for th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></sp=
an> and <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> while using=
 the Service-Type attribute method for the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>, create two external authent=
ication objects that identify the same RADIUS
                                             server: one object includes th=
e predefined <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000494"=
>CLI Access Filter</span> users (for use with the <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>), and the other object leaves the <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000494_d3031e202a1310">CLI Acc=
ess Filter</span> empty (for use with <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"=
>Firepower Threat Defense</span></span>s).
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>

_91EF10ECE6554C49B66A3EAC724E64E8">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63677__=
ID-2263-000002a4">In <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span=
>, choose <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol"> Users</span>=
</span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>

_DE9E817D2129423B92BFCC910AC85E33">

ID-2263-000002a7">Click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-226=

r=3D"0">

ass=3D"ph uicontrol">Primary Server</span>, enter a <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000002c2">Host Name/IP Address</span>.=20

d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">

content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p" id=3D"=
id_63677__ID-2263-000002c311">If you are using a certificate to connect via=
 TLS
                                                         or SSL, the host n=
ame in the certificate must match the host name used

addition, IPv6 addresses are not supported for
                                                         encrypted connecti=
ons.=20

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

r=3D"0">

pand">

                                             <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enter the =
<span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000003bb">Timeout</spa=
n> in
                                                seconds before retrying the=
 primary server, between 1 and 300. The
                                                default is 30.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <section class=3D"itemgroup in=
fo">
                                               =20

                                            =20

fo">
                                               =20
                                                <div class=3D"tableContaine=
r"><table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">

                                                      <td width=3D"1%" clas=
s=3D"td_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                         <p><b>Note</b></p>=
&nbsp;
                                                      </td>
                                                      <td border=3D"0" clas=
s=3D"td_faq">
                                                         <section class=3D"=
note__content">
                                                           =20
                                                            <p class=3D"p">=
The timeout range is different for the FTD and the FMC, so if you
                                                               share an obj=
ect, be sure not to exceed the FTD's smaller timeout
                                                               range (1-300=
 seconds). If you set the timeout to a higher value,
                                                               the FTD RADI=
US configuration will not work.

pand">

<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Retries</span> before rolling over to the

is 3.

                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"id_63677__=
ID-2263-00000490">(Optional) Instead of using RADIUS-defined users (see Ste=
p <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/=
firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_device=
.html#id_63677__step_define_users">Step&nbsp;1</a>), in the <span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000494_d3031e345a1310">CLI Access
                                             Filter</span> area
                                          <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=
=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000668">Administrator CLI
                                             Access User List</span> field,=
 enter the user names that should have CLI access,
                                          separated by commas. For example,=
 enter <kbd class=3D"ph userinput">jchrichton, aerynsun,
                                             rygel</kbd>.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">You may want to us=
e the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000494_d3031e3=
59a1310">CLI Access Filter</span> method for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> so you can use the same exte=
rnal authentication object with <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Threat Defense</span></span> and other platform types.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">If you=
 want to use RADIUS-defined users, you must leave the <span class=3D"ph uic=
ontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000494_d3031e375a1310">CLI Access
                                                            Filter</span>
                                                         empty.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">Make sure that the=
se usernames match usernames on the RADIUS server. The
                                             names must be Linux-valid user=
names:
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                          <ul class=3D"ul">
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Maximum 32 a=
lphanumeric characters, plus hyphen (-) and underscore
                                                   (_)
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">All lowercas=
e</p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Cannot start=
 with hyphen (-); cannot be all numbers; cannot include <span class=3D"ph">=
at sign (@) or slash (/)</span></p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                            =20
                                          </ul>
                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Note</b></p>&nbsp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p">Users =
with CLI access can gain Linux shell access with the
                                                         <span class=3D"key=
word cmdname">expert</span> command. Linux shell users can obtain root
                                                         privileges, which =
can present a security risk. Make sure that you
                                                         restrict the list =
of users with CLI or Linux shell
                                                         access.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>

r=3D"0">

class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> connectivity to the RADIUS server.=20

only test <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> connectiv=
ity to the RADIUS server; there is no test function for managed

IUS server.

                                         =20

r=3D"0">

an also enter <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Additional Test Parameters</span=
> to test user credentials for a user who should be able to authenticate: e=
nter a <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">User Name</span> and <span class=3D"ph =
uicontrol">Password</span>, and then click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Tes=
t</span>.
                                       </p>

                                         =20
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
