                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                     =20
                                                      <p class=3D"p" id=3D"=
id_63677__ID-2263-000006cb">If you mistype the name or password of the test=
 user, the test fails even if the server configuration is correct. To verif=
y
                                                         that the server co=
nfiguration is correct, click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__=
ID-2263-000006cd">Test</span> without entering user information in the <spa=
n class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000006ce">Additional Test =
Parameters</span> field first. If that succeeds, supply a user name and pas=
sword to test with the specific user.
                                                      </p>
                                                     =20
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp"=
>
                                          <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                             <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=
=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h4>
                                          </section>
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">To test if you can=
 retrieve the <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000004ca">J=
Smith</code> user credentials at the Example company, enter <code class=3D"=
ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000004cb">JSmith</code> and the correct =
password.=20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;15</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol">Save</span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;16</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Enable use of th=
is server. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/d=
ocs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/platfor=
m_settings_for_firepower_threat_defense.html#task_hx5_5hy_1cb">Configure Ex=
ternal Authentication for SSH</a></p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"example" id=3D"id_63677__examp=
le_5152AF79302D45F8AC731EEBEEC48025">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Examples</h4=
>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Simple =
User Role Assignments</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
87">The following figure illustrates a sample RADIUS login
                                 authentication object for a server running=
 Cisco Identity Services Engine (ISE) with
                                 an IP address of 10.10.10.98 on port 1812.=
 No backup server is defined.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456091.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456091.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
87_d3031e505a1310">The following example shows RADIUS-specific parameters,
                                 including the timeout (30 seconds) and num=
ber of failed retries before the Firepower
                                 System attempts to contact the backup serv=
er, if any.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
88">This example illustrates important aspects of RADIUS user role
                                 configuration:=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
89">Users <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-0000058b">ewhar=
ton</code> and
                                 <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__=
ID-2263-0000058c">gsand</code> are granted web interface
                                 Administrative access.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
8e">The user <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000590">cb=
ronte</code> is
                                 granted web interface Maintenance User acc=
ess.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
92">The user <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000594">ja=
usten</code> is
                                 granted web interface Security Analyst acc=
ess.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
96">The user <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-00000598">ew=
harton</code> can
                                 log into the device using a CLI account.=
=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456092.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456092.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
99">The following graphic depicts the role configuration for the
                                 example:=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><strong class=3D"ph b">Roles f=
or Users Matching an Attribute-Value Pair</strong></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
9f">You can use an attribute-value pair to identify users who
                                 should receive a particular user role. If =
the attribute you use is a custom
                                 attribute, you must define the custom attr=
ibute.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
a0">The following figure illustrates the role configuration and
                                 custom attribute definition in a sample RA=
DIUS login authentication object for the
                                 same ISE server as in the previous example=
.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005=
a1">In this example, however, the <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677_=
_ID-2263-000005a2">MS-RAS-Version</code> custom attribute is returned for o=
ne or more of the
                                 users because a Microsoft remote access se=
rver is in use. Note the <code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-=
000005a3">MS-RAS-Version</code> custom attribute is a string. In
                                 this example, all users logging in to RADI=
US through a Microsoft v. 5.00 remote
                                 access server should receive the Security =
Analyst (Read Only) role, so you enter the
                                 attribute-value pair of <code class=3D"ph =
codeph" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005a4">MS-RAS-Version=3DMSRASV5.00</code=
> in the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"id_63677__ID-2263-000005a5">Sec=
urity Analyst (Read Only)</span> field.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://www.cisco.c=
om/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456093.jpg" c=
lass=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or screenshot."><=
img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-50=
0000/450001-460000/456001-457000/456093.jpg"></a></p>
                             =20
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title15" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_63679">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
5">Enable External Authentication for Users on FTD Devices</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">Enable External Authentication in=
 the Firepower Threat Defense Platform Settings, and then deploy
                              the settings to the managed devices. See <a c=
lass=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepo=
wer/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/platform_settings_for_fire=
power_threat_defense.html#task_hx5_5hy_1cb">Configure External Authenticati=
on for SSH</a> for more information.
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title16" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title16">=
Troubleshooting LDAP Authentication Connections</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        	=09
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_=
qcb__d1258e12">
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d125=
8e14">If you create an LDAP authentication object and it either does
                              				not succeed in connecting to the server y=
ou select, or does not retrieve the list of
                              				users you want, you can tune the settings=
 in the object.=20
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d125=
8e17">If the connection fails when you test it, try the following
                              				suggestions to troubleshoot your configur=
ation:=20
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e22">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e24">Use the messages displayed at the top of the web
                                    						interface screen and in the test =
output to determine which areas of the
                                    						object are causing the issue.
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e28">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e30">Check that the user name and password you used for the
                                    						object are valid:=20
                                 </p>
                                 				=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e35">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e37">Check that you have the rights to browse to the directory=
 indicated in your base-distinguished name by connecting to the LDAP
                                          server using a third-party LDAP b=
rowser.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e41">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e43">Check that the user name is unique to the
                                          								directory information tre=
e for the LDAP server.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e47">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e49">If you see an LDAP bind error 49 in the test
                                          								output, the user binding =
for the user failed. Try authenticating to
                                          								the server through a thir=
d-party application to see if the binding
                                          								fails through that connec=
tion as well.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    				=09
                                 </ul>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e55">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e57">Check that you have correctly identified the server: </p>
                                 				=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e62">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e64">Check that the server IP address or host name
                                          								is correct.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e68">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e70">Check that you have TCP/IP access from your
                                          								local appliance to the au=
thentication server where you want to
                                          								connect.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e74">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e76">Check that access to the server is not blocked
                                          								by a firewall and that th=
e port you have configured in the object is
                                          								open.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e80">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e82">If you are using a certificate to connect via
                                          								TLS or SSL, the host name=
 in the certificate must match the host
                                          								name used for the server.=
=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e86">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e88">Check that you have not used an IPv6 address
                                          								for the server connection=
 if you are authenticating CLI access.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e93">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e95">If you used server type defaults, check that
                                          								you have the correct serv=
er type and click <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e97">Set Defaults</span> again to reset
                                          								the default values.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    				=09
                                 </ul>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e104">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e106">If you typed in your base-distinguished name, click <span clas=
s=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d1258e108">Fetch DNs</span>=
 to retrieve all the available base distinguished names on the server, and =
select the name from the list.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e113">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e115">If you are using any filters, access attributes, or
                                    						advanced settings, check that eac=
h is valid and typed correctly.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e120">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e122">If you are using any filters, access attributes, or
                                    						advanced settings, try removing e=
ach setting and testing the object without
                                    						it.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e126">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e128">If you are using a base filter or a <span class=3D"ph">CLI</sp=
an> access filter, make sure that the filter is enclosed in
                                    						parentheses and that you are usin=
g a valid comparison operator (maximum 450
                                    						characters, including the enclosi=
ng parentheses).=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e135">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e137">To test a more restricted base filter, try setting it
                                    						to the base distinguished name fo=
r the user to retrieve just that user.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb_=
_d1258e141">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e143">If you are using an encrypted connection: </p>
                                 				=09
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e148">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e150">Check that the name of the LDAP server in the
                                          								certificate matches the h=
ost name that you use to connect.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    					=09
                                    <li class=3D"li" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e154">
                                       						=09
                                       <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_k=
yq_qcb__d1258e156">Check that you have not used an IPv6 address
                                          								with an encrypted server =
connection.=20
                                       </p>
                                       					=09
                                    </li>
                                    				=09
                                 </ul>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e164">If you are using a test user, make sure that the user
                                    						name and password are typed corre=
ctly.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e170">If you are using a test user, remove the user
                                    						credentials and test the object.=
=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              			=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb=
__d1258e177">Test the query that you are using by connecting to the LDAP se=
rver and using this syntax: </p>
                                 					<pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>
ldapsearch -x -b 'base_distinguished_name'
-h LDAPserver_ip_address -p port -v -D
'user_distinguished_name' -W 'base_filter'

</code></pre>
                                 					<p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_ky=
q_qcb__d1258e183">For example, if you are trying to connect to the
                                    						security domain on <code class=3D=
"ph codeph" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d1258e185">myrtle.example.com</cod=
e>
                                    						using the <code class=3D"ph codep=
h" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d1258e188">domainadmin@myrtle.example.com</=
code> user and a base filter of
                                    							(<code class=3D"ph codeph" id=3D=
"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d1258e191">cn=3D*</code>), you could test the
                                    						connection using this statement:=
=20
                                 </p>
                                 					<pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>
ldapsearch -x -b 'CN=3Dsecurity,DC=3Dmyrtle,DC=3Dexample,DC=3Dcom'
-h myrtle.example.com -p 389 -v -D
'domainadmin@myrtle.example.com' -W '(cn=3D*)'

</code></pre>
                                 				</li>
                              		=09
                           </ul>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d125=
8e200">If you can test your connection successfully but authentication
                              				does not work after you deploy a platform=
 settings policy, check that authentication
                              				and the object you want to use are both e=
nabled in the platform settings policy that
                              				is applied to the device.=20
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"reference_lzr_kyq_qcb__d125=
8e203">If you connect successfully but want to adjust the list of users
                              				retrieved by your connection, you can add=
 or change a base filter or <span class=3D"ph">CLI</span> access filter or =
use a more restrictive or less restrictive base DN.=20
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">While authenticating a connection=
 to Active Directory (AD) server, rarely the connection event log indicates=
 blocked LDAP
                              traffic although the connection to AD server =
is successful. This incorrect connection log occurs when the AD server send=
s
                              a duplicate reset packet. The <span class=3D"=
ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> device identi=
fies the second reset packet as part of a new connection request and logs t=
he connection with Block action.
                           </p>
                           	=09
                        </section>
                        =09
